ECE 3300 Lab 6 – Dual BCD Up/Down Counters, ALU, and Control Display on 7-Segment Display

Members: Jetts Crittenden & Evan Tram

Objective: Two independent BCD up/down counters (units & tens), each with its own direction bit.
            A simple 4‑bit ALU that can add or subtract those two BCD values.
            A control-display digit bundling four control bits into one 4-bit nibble:
            SW5–SW6 = ALU operation (00=add, 01=sub)
            SW7 = units counter direction (1=up, 0=down)
            SW8 = tens counter direction (1=up, 0=down)
            A 3‑digit 7‑segment display:
            Digit AN0: result low nibble (result[3:0])
            Digit AN1: result high nibble (result[7:4])
            Digit AN2: control nibble {SW8, SW7, SW6, SW5}
            Debug LEDs:
            LED[3:0] = units counter BCD
            LED[7:4] = tens counter BCD

Video Demo: https://youtu.be/tDmsNwrCuAU?si=6XTLR6KtyroO18NP  
